9 Apr 2015: Half of all Ebola infections in Sierra Leone-Guinea border area
http://www.news24.com/Africa/News/WHO-Half-of-all-Ebola-infections-in-S-Leone-Guinea-border-area-20150409
[According to the World Health Organization, almost 50 percent of all Ebola infections in West Africa have been in 2 districts located in the border region between Sierra Leone and Guinea. WHO is now focusing its efforts on Kambia in western Sierra Leone and Forecariah in eastern Guinea]

[The good news is that Kailahun district (Sierra Leone), a former epicentre of the epidemic, has been Ebola-free for more than 112 days now. - Mod.LK]

10 Apr 2015: Risk of Ebola spreading to other countries appears to be falling - World Health Organization
