http://www.trust.org/item/20150409192255-v7nwq/
[A report by Liberia's anti-corruption monitor, the General Auditing Commission, found some USD 800 000 of Ebola funding spent at the height of the outbreak last year [2014] was not properly accounted for, most of it passing through the defense ministry. USD 13 million was spent by the National Ebola Trust Fund (NETF), the majority of which came from foreign donations. The audit did not include donations from international organizations including the World Bank, the United States Agency for International Development (USAID), and other foreign donors whose contribution did not flow through the NETF.]

